\begin_layout Standard
This architecture can be used to infer about a proposition by using the relationships to calculate the joint probability of the proposition across the nodes of the BN.
 This makes them ideal for scenario testing in forensic investigations 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citep
key "Vlek2015"
literal "false"

\end_inset

.
 DAGs are versatile constructs,
 not restricted to just forensic science.
 Ongoing use is common in many fields,
 including epidemiology 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citep
key "TaylorH2024"
literal "false"

\end_inset

,
 construction 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citep
key "Sridhar2024"
literal "false"

\end_inset

,
 compiler design ,
 process/data flow mapping 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citep
key "Astronomer2024"
literal "false"

\end_inset

,
 cryptocurrency,
 and more 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citep
key "BiedermanTaroni2012"
literal "false"

\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
As vertices are treated as independent random variables following a multinomial distribution,
 the likelihood values within a Bayesian Network can be described using a named probability distribution,
 the Dirichlet distribution.,
 The Dirichlet distribution is a multivariate generalisation of the Beta distribution and acts as a conjugate prior distribution for the multinomial distribution
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citep
key "kotz_chapter_2019"
literal "false"

\end_inset

.
 Using a value of one for the concentration parameter (denoted by the Greek letter α) of a Dirichlet distribution is equivalent to using a multivariate version of a uniform flat prior distribution to allow a situation where no prior knowledge is known
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citep
key "Taylor2016,kotz_chapter_2019"
literal "false"

\end_inset

.
 This can be used to test sensitivity of the resultant LR to the CPT information that is used in a given vertex 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citep
key "kotz_chapter_2019,Taylor2016"
literal "false"

\end_inset

.
\end_layout

